    "thinking": "The user wants me to generate 10 unique, secure passwords that are exactly 14 characters long, with specific requirements:\n1. 14 characters total\n2. At least 2 uppercase letters\n3. At least 3 digits\n4. At least 2 special characters\n\nI need to write a Python script to generate these passwords and ensure they meet the criteria. Let me think about how to approach this:\n\n1. Define character sets:\n   - Uppercase letters: 'ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZ'\n   - Digits: '0123456789'\n   - Special characters: '!@#$%^&*()_+-=[]{}|;:,.<>?' (or similar)\n   - Lowercase letters: 'abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz' (for variety)\n\n2. For each password:\n   - Start by ensuring we have at least 2 uppercase, 3 digits, and 2 special characters\n   - Then fill the remaining positions with any character type (uppercase, lowercase, digits, special)\n   - Make sure all 10 passwords are unique\n\n3. Use random.choice to select characters from each set\n\nLet me write a Python script to do this:\n\n```python\nimport random\nimport string\n\ndef generate_password():\n    # Define character sets\n    uppercase_letters = string.ascii_uppercase\n    digits = string.digits\n    special_characters = '!@#$%^&*()_+-=[]{}|;:,.<>?'  # Common special characters\n    lowercase_letters = string.ascii_lowercase\n    \n    # Ensure minimum requirements\n    password_chars = []\n    \n    # Add at least 2 uppercase letters\n    password_chars.extend(random.sample(uppercase_letters, 2))\n    \n    # Add at least 3 digits\n    password_chars.extend(random.sample(digits, 3))\n    \n    # Add at least 2 special characters\n    password_chars.extend(random.sample(special_characters, 2))\n    \n    # Fill remaining positions (14 - 2 - 3 - 2 = 7)\n    remaining_count = 14 - (2 + 3 + 2)\n    all_chars = uppercase_letters + digits + special_characters + lowercase_letters\n    \n    # Add remaining characters randomly\n    password_chars.extend(random.choices(all_chars, k=remaining_count))\n    \n    # Shuffle to mix the characters\n    random.shuffle(password_chars)\n    \n    # Convert list to string\n    return ''.join(password_chars)\n\ndef generate_unique_passwords(count):\n    passwords = set()\n    while len(passwords) < count:\n        pwd = generate_password()\n        passwords.add(pwd)\n    return list(passwords)\n\n# Generate 10 unique passwords\nunique_passwords = generate_unique_passwords(10)\nfor i, pwd in enumerate(unique_passwords, 1):\n    print(f\"{i}. {pwd}\")\n```\n\nWait, I should also verify that each password meets the criteria. Let me add a verification function to be sure:\n\n```python\nimport random\nimport string\n\ndef generate_password():\n    # Define character sets\n    uppercase_letters = string.ascii_uppercase\n    digits = string.digits\n    special_characters = '!@#$%^&*()_+-=[]{}|;:,.<>?'  # Common special characters\n    lowercase_letters = string.ascii_lowercase\n    \n    # Ensure minimum requirements\n    password_chars = []\n    \n    # Add at least 2 uppercase letters\n    password_chars.extend(random.sample(uppercase_letters, 2))\n    \n    # Add at least 3 digits\n    password_chars.extend(random.sample(digits, 3))\n    \n    # Add at least 2 special characters\n    password_chars.extend(random.sample(special_characters, 2))\n    \n    # Fill remaining positions (14 - 2 - 3 - 2 = 7)\n    remaining_count = 14 - (2 + 3 + 2)\n    all_chars = uppercase_letters + digits + special_characters + lowercase_letters\n    \n    # Add remaining characters randomly\n    password_chars.extend(random.choices(all_chars, k=remaining_count))\n    \n    # Shuffle to mix the characters\n    random.shuffle(password_chars)\n    \n    # Convert list to string\n    return ''.join(password_chars)\n\ndef verify_password(password):\n    # Check length\n    if len(password) != 14:\n        return False\n    \n    # Check at least 2 uppercase letters\n    if sum(1 for c in password if c.isupper()) < 2:\n        return False\n    \n    # Check at least 3 digits\n    if sum(1 for c in password if c.isdigit()) < 3:\n        return False\n    \n    # Check at least 2 special characters\n    special_chars = '!@#$%^&*()_+-=[]{}|;:,.<>?'  # Same as defined\n    if sum(1 for c in password if c in special_chars) < 2:\n        return False\n    \n    return True\n\ndef generate_unique_passwords(count):\n    passwords = set()\n    while len(passwords) < count:\n        pwd = generate_password()\n        # Verify before adding to ensure it meets criteria\n        if verify_password(pwd):\n            passwords.add(pwd)\n    return list(passwords)\n\n# Generate 10 unique passwords\nunique_passwords = generate_unique_passwords(10)\nfor i, pwd in enumerate(unique_passwords, 1):\n    print(f\"{i}. {pwd}\")\n```\n\nThis script should work. Let me run it to get the actual passwords.\n"
